## Introduction {#intro}

Djot is a lightweight markup language designed as an improved alternative to Markdown[^djot]. It offers:

- Clear, unambiguous syntax
- Extensive features
- Better handling of edge cases

[^djot]: Created by John MacFarlane, author of Pandoc.

### Why Djot?

> Djot provides the power of extended Markdown
> with fewer surprises and better consistency.

Visit the [official site](https://djot.net) or check the [specification][spec].

[spec]: https://htmlpreview.github.io/?https://github.com/jgm/djot/blob/master/doc/syntax.html

## Text Formatting {#formatting}

### Basic Emphasis

- _Italic text_ for emphasis
- *Bold text* for strong emphasis
- _Combined *bold* in italic_

### Extended Formatting

- {=Highlighted text=} for marking
- ^Superscript^ for mathematical notation: x^2^
- ~Subscript~ for formulas: H~2~O
- {+Inserted text+} for additions
- {-Deleted text-} for removals

### Smart Punctuation

Djot handles punctuation intelligently:

- Ellipsis: waiting...
- Em dash: A final thought---and then nothing
- En dash: Pages 23--45

### Escaping

Sometimes you need literal characters: \*not bold\*, \`not code\`, \_not italic\_.

Line breaks work too\
like this continuation.

