### Attributes

Attributes can be applied to many elements:

- Headings: `# Title {#id}`
- Links: [example](url){.external}
- Spans: [custom text]{.highlight #unique}
- Code blocks: ``` rust {.highlight}

### Comments

Comments in attributes: {#id % this won't be visible % .class}

Multiple comments: {%note% .class %another note%}

### Forced Delimiters

For edge cases where automatic matching fails:

Normal: _emphasis_ and *strong*

Forced: {_forced emphasis with {*strong*} inside_}

### Footnotes {#footnotes}

Basic footnote[^1] in text.

Multiple footnotes[^2] can be[^custom] used[^final].

[^1]: First footnote with simple content.
[^2]: Second footnote with _formatting_ and `code`.
[^custom]: Custom label instead of number.
[^final]: Last footnote with math: $`x^2 + y^2 = z^2`

